French Onion Dip
  --Cook's Country

3 tbsp unsalted butter
2 lb onion, chopped fine
salt and pepper
1/8 tsp cayenne pepper
1/4 c water
2 1/2 tsp basalmic vinegar
1 c sour cream
1/2 c mayo

Melt butter in 12" skillet over medium heat. Add onions, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/2 tsp pepper, and cayenne and cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are translucent, ~10 min. Reduce heat to medium low and continue cooking until onions are golden, ~10 min. Add 2 tbsp water to skillet and cook, scraping up any fond, until water is evaoprated, ~5 min. Add remaining 2 tbsp water and cook until onions are caramelized and water is evaoprated, ~5 min longer. Remove from heat and stir in vinegar. Transfer onions to medium bowl and let cool for 10 min. Add sour cream and mayo to onions and stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate for at least 30 min to allow flavors to blend. Serve. Can make up to 24 hrs in advance.
